            <article id="post2" class="blog-post">
                <h2>Battle Of Bessang Pass - March 1944 - June 1944, Phillipines.</h2>
              <section id="post1-section1">
                <p>There's an oft-overlooked battle in the Pacific theatre of WW2 in the Phillipines called "The Battle Of Bessang Pass" during the Allied liberation of the Phillipines. This battle was something of a tug-of-war between the Filipino Guerillas and the defending Japanese. I'll be using <a href="https://wargameds.com/products/philippines-44">Panzer Campaigns Phillipines '44</a> to illustrate.</p>
		<br>
		<p>The Bessang Pass was part of a defensive line in the mountains off the west coast of Luzon. It led directly from the coast to the mountainous regions, and so was a key point to the integrity of the defensive line.</p>
		<img src="/wargames/screens/bessangpass1.jpg" alt="Bessang Pass map">

		<p><a href="https://wargameds.com/products/philippines-44">Phillipines '44</a> covers the 3 major parts of the battle over the 4 month period beginning with:</p>
		<h3>Initial filipino guerilla attack - March 29th 1945</h3>
		<img src="/wargames/screens/battlebessang1.jpg" alt="Battle Of Bessang in March">
		<h3>Japanese counter-attack - May 17th 1945</h3>
		<img src="/wargames/screens/battlebessang2.jpg" alt="Battle Of Bessang in May">
		<h3>The final push to successfully secure the Bessang Pass - June 10th to June 14th 1945</h3>
		<img src="/wargames/screens/bessangpass3.jpg" alt="Battle Of Bessang in June">

              </section>
            </article>
